snippet.title: Amber Heard 'had no evidence of any injuries when police arrived after call
snippet.description:
Amber Heard 'had no evidence of any injuries when police arrived after call
It is said officers arriving at her apartment didn't see any signs of injury
Amber Heard reportedly showed no evidence of any injuries when police arrived at her home on Saturday night.
The actress - who has been granted a temporary restraining order against Johnny Depp after accusing him of physically assaulting her - is said to have refused to file a police report, and at the time did not allege any brutality.
According to TMZ, officers arrived at her home on Saturday but saw no injury, and left after she refused to offer any more information.
Meanwhile, the website reports that the judge has ruled Depp is required to stay 100 yards away from his wife - which is made easier by him being in Europe currently to promote his movie
The website adds that she has the right to live in their family home, although other requests - including an order to keep Depp away from at least one of their pet dogs - was rejected.

In a picture submitted to the court in Los Angeles and first published by showbiz website TMZ , Amber can be seen with bruises around her eyes.

TMZ says that Amber is claiming Depp - who was represented by his lawyer - hit her in the face on Saturday night with an iPhone before police were called.

It is said she refused to give a statement to police, who have given her a number to call if she changes her mind.

In legal documents obtained by TMZ, Heard - who had bruising around her eye as she left court on Friday - accuses him of drug and alcohol abuse, alleging he turned up to her birthday party last month "inebriated and high"
